{
  "texts": [
    "The reviewed articles in the current study were also conducted in well-developed Western countries.",
    "It is unclear whether underdeveloped areas may benefit more from low-cost, online based interventions for mental health issues.",
    "ConclusionAs a potential solution to the problem of prolonged waiting lists for psychotherapy, this systematic review examined the effectiveness of DMHIs in reducing anxiety and depression symptoms of patients on waiting lists for psychotherapy.",
    "Our results showed that among the RCTs, DMHIs were overall not more effective when compared with simply waiting or the control groups who used a self-help book.",
    "Among the non-RCTs, although the intervention reduced depression and anxiety symptoms, the study design with no control group made it difficult to conclude the effectiveness of the intervention."
  ]
}